title: my_esphome_energymonitor
content:
esphome:
  name: "esphome-energymonitor-1"
  friendly_name: EnergyMonitor_1
  on_boot:
    then:
    - pulse_meter.set_total_pulses:
        id: count
        value: !lambda "return id(total_pulses);"

esp8266:
  board: nodemcuv2
  restore_from_flash: true 

globals:
  - id: total_pulses
    type: float
    restore_value: yes

logger:


ota:


wifi:
  ssid: !secret wifi_ssid
  password: !secret wifi_password

  # Enable fallback hotspot (captive portal) in case wifi connection fails
  ap:
    ssid: "Esphome-Web-fafafa"
    password: "fafafa"

captive_portal:
    
mqtt:
  broker: 10.11.12.13
  port: 1883
  username: admin
  password: !secret mqtt_password
  discovery: true
  on_connect:
    - mqtt.publish:
        topic: energymonitorstatus
        payload: online
        retain: true
  # topic_prefix: esphome/energymonitor/01
  birth_message:
    topic: energymonitorstatus
    payload: online
    retain: true
  will_message:
    topic: energymonitorstatus 
    payload: offline
    retain: true
  on_message:
    topic: total
    then:
      - pulse_meter.set_total_pulses:
          id: count
          value: !lambda "return atof(x.c_str()) / 0.0003125;"


preferences:
  flash_write_interval: 5min

sensor:
  - platform: pulse_meter
    pin: D7
    unit_of_measurement: 'kW'
    name: 'Electricity Usage'
    id: count
    internal_filter: 100ms
    accuracy_decimals: 3
    retain: true
    filters:
      - multiply: 0.01875 #=1/(3200/60)
    on_value:
      - mqtt.publish:
          topic: esphome/energymonitor/01/count
          payload: !lambda |-
            return to_string(id(count).state);
    total:
      name: "Electricity Total"
      id: total
      unit_of_measurement: "kWh"
      accuracy_decimals: 3
      filters:
        - multiply: 0.0003125 #=1/3200
      retain: true
      on_value:
        - mqtt.publish:
            retain: true
            topic: esphome/energymonitor/01/total
            payload: !lambda |-
              id(total_pulses) = id(total).raw_state;
              return to_string(id(total).state);

		</repository>
	</repositories>

	<dependencies>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>io.papermc.paper</groupId>
			<artifactId>paper-api</artifactId>
			<version>1.17.1-R0.1-SNAPSHOT</version>
			<scope>provided</scope>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>com.github.MilkBowl</groupId>
			<artifactId>VaultAPI</artifactId>
			<version>1.7</version>
			<scope>provided</scope>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>me.snakeamazing.blossom</groupId>
			<artifactId>bukkit</artifactId>
			<version>0.3.10</version>
			<scope>compile</scope>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>net.kyori</groupId>
			<artifactId>adventure-platform-bukkit</artifactId>
			<version>4.3.0</version>
			<scope>compile</scope>
		 </dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>dev.triumphteam</groupId>
			<artifactId>triumph-cmd-bukkit</artifactId>
			<version>2.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
			<scope>compile</scope>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>net.kyori</groupId>
			<artifactId>adventure-api</artifactId>
			<version>4.14.0</version>
			<scope>compile</scope>
		 </dependency>
		 <dependency>
			<groupId>net.kyori</groupId>
			<artifactId>adventure-text-minimessage</artifactId>
			<version>4.14.0</version>
			<scope>compile</scope>
		 </dependency>
	</dependencies>

	<build>
		<plugins>
			<plugin>
				<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
				<artifactId>maven-install-plugin</artifactId>
				<version>3.1.1</version>
			</plugin>
			<plugin>
				<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
				<artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
				<version>3.11.0</version>
				<configuration>
					<source>${maven.compiler.source}</source>
					<target>${maven.compiler.target}</target>
				</configuration>
			</plugin>
			<plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-shade-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.5.0</version>
                <configuration>
                    <filters>
                        <filter>
                            <artifact>*</artifact>
                            <excludes>
                                <exclude>META-INF/*.MF</exclude>
                            </excludes>
                        </filter>
                    </filters>
                    <minimizeJar>true</minimizeJar>
                    <relocations>
						<relocation>
							<pattern>dev.triumphteam.cmd</pattern>
							<shadedPattern>es.obsilion.coinflip.shaded.cmd</shadedPattern> <!-- Replace package here -->
						</relocation>
						<relocation>
							<pattern>net.kyori.adventure</pattern>
							<shadedPattern>es.obsilion.coinflip.shaded.kyori</shadedPattern> <!-- Replace package here -->
						</relocation>
                        <relocation>
                            <pattern>me.snakeamazing.blossom</pattern>
                            <shadedPattern>es.obsilion.coinflip.shaded.blossom</shadedPattern>
                        </relocation>
                    </relocations>
                </configuration>
                <executions>
                    <execution>
                        <phase>package</phase>
                        <goals>
                            <goal>shade</goal>
                        </goals>
                    </execution>
                </executions>
            </plugin>
			<plugin>
				<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
				<artifactId>maven-resources-plugin</artifactId>
				<version>3.3.1</version>
			</plugin>
		</plugins>
		<resources>
			<resource>
				<directory>src/main/resources</directory>
				<filtering>true</filtering>
			</resource>
		</resources>
	</build>

	<profiles>
		<profile>
			<id>warnings</id>
			<properties>
				<maven.plugin.validation>VERBOSE</maven.plugin.validation>
			</properties>
		</profile>
	</profiles>
</project>

title: switch
content:
---
anchors:
  text: &header
    val: "Multiple windows in the same dialog can be used to provide step by step user data input.\n"

windows:
  MAIN:
    widgets:
      - text: *header
      - text: "Step 1. Press Next"
      - next: null
      - start: !include components/menu_button.yaml
  INPUT:
    widgets:
      - text: *header
      - text: "Step 2. Select options"
      - checkbox:
          checked: "✓ Option is enabled"
          unchecked: "Click to enable the option"
          default: false
          id: chk
      - radio:
          checked: "🔘 {item}"
          unchecked: "⚪️ {item}"
          items: [😆, 😱, 😈, 🤖, 🤡]
          item_id_getter: item_id_getter
          id: emoji
      - row:
          buttons:
            - back: null
            - next: null
      - start: !include components/menu_button.yaml
  LAST:
    getter: data_getter
    widgets:
      - text: *header
      - text: "Step 3. Your data:"
      - case:
          texts: {
            true: "Option: enabled",
            false: "Option: disabled"
          }
          selector: option
      - format: "Selected emoji: {emoji}"
      - back: null
      - start: !include components/menu_button.yaml
...

title: selects
content:
---
anchors:
  back_to_main_menu: &back_button
    id: back
    text: "Back"
    state: Selects:MAIN

windows:
  MAIN:
    widgets:
      - text: "Different keyboard Selects."
      - switch_to:
          text: "Select"
          id: select
          state: Selects:SELECT
      - switch_to:
          text: "Radio"
          id: radio
          state: Selects:RADIO
      - switch_to:
          text: "Multiselect"
          id: multiselect
          state: Selects:MULTI
      - start: !include components/menu_button.yaml
  SELECT:
    getter: getter
    widgets:
      - text: "Select widget"
      - list:
          field: "+ {item.name} - {item.id}"
          items: fruits
      - column:
          buttons:
            - select:
                format: "{item.name} ({item.id})"
                id: sel
                items: fruits
                item_id_getter: fruit_id_getter
                on_click: on_item_selected
      - switch_to: *back_button
  RADIO:
    getter: getter
    widgets:
      - text: "Radio widget"
      - column:
          buttons:
            - radio:
                checked: "🔘 {item.name}"
                unchecked: "⚪️ {item.name}"
                id: radio
                items: fruits
                item_id_getter: fruit_id_getter
      - switch_to: *back_button
  MULTI:
    getter: getter
    widgets:
      - text: "Multiselect widget"
      - column:
          buttons:
            - multi_select:
                checked: "✓ {item.name}"
                unchecked: "{item.name}"
                id: multi
                items: fruits
                item_id_getter: fruit_id_getter
      - switch_to: *back_button
...

title: scrolls
content:
---
anchors:
  back_to_main_menu: &back_button
    id: back
    text: "Back"
    state: Scrolls:MAIN
  multi_select: &multi_select
    checked: "✓ {item[0]}"
    unchecked: "  {item[0]}"
    id: ms
    items: products
    item_id_getter: 1

windows:
  MAIN:
    widgets:
      - text: "Scrolling variant demo. Please, select an option:"
      - switch_to:
          text: "📜 Default Pager"
          id: default
          state: Scrolls:DEFAULT_PAGER
      - switch_to:
          text: "📑 Customised pager"
          id: pagers
          state: Scrolls:PAGERS
      - switch_to:
          text: "📄 Text scroll"
          id: text
          state: Scrolls:TEXT
      - switch_to:
          text: "📟 StubScroll (getter-based)"
          id: stub
          state: Scrolls:STUB
      - start: !include components/menu_button.yaml
  DEFAULT_PAGER:
    getter: product_getter
    widgets:
      - text: "Scrolling group with default pager (legacy mode)"
      - scrolling_group: &scrolling_group
          width: 1
          height: 5
          id: scroll_with_pager
          buttons:
            - multi_select: *multi_select
      - switch_to: *back_button
  PAGERS:
    getter: product_getter
    widgets:
      - text: "Scrolling group with external paging controls"
      - numbered_pager:
          scroll: scroll_no_pager
          page_text: "{target_page1}\uFE0F\u20E3"
          current_page_text: "{current_page1}"
      - numbered_pager: scroll_no_pager
      - scrolling_group:
          width: 1
          height: 5
          hide_pager: true
          id: scroll_no_pager
          buttons:
            - multi_select: *multi_select
      - row:
          buttons:
            - first_page:
                scroll: scroll_no_pager
                text: "⏮️ {target_page1}"
            - prev_page:
                scroll: scroll_no_pager
                text: "◀️"
            - current_page:
                scroll: scroll_no_pager
                text: "{current_page1}"
            - next_page:
                scroll: scroll_no_pager
                text: "▶️"
            - last_page:
                scroll: scroll_no_pager
                text: "{target_page1} ⏭️"
      - row:
          buttons:
            - prev_page: scroll_no_pager
            - next_page: scroll_no_pager
            - switch_to: *back_button
  TEXT:
    widgets:
      - text: "Text scrolling:\n"
      - scrolling_text:
          text: !include components/very_long_text.yaml
          id: text_scroll
          page_size: 1000
      - numbered_pager: text_scroll
      - switch_to: *back_button
  STUB:
    getter: paging_getter
    widgets:
      - text: "Stub Scroll. Getter is used to paginate\n"
      - format: "You are at page {current_page} of {pages}"
      - format: "Day by number is {day}"
      - static_media:
          path: "media/{current_page}.png"
      - stub_scroll:
          id: stub_scroll
          pages: pages
      - numbered_pager: stub_scroll
      - switch_to: *back_button
...

title: layouts
content:
---
anchors:
  back_to_main_menu: &back_button
    id: back
    text: "Back"
    state: Layouts:MAIN
  select: &fruits_select
    format: "{item}"
    id: sel
    items: ["Apple", "Banana", "Orange", "Pear"]
    item_id_getter: get_fruit_item
  button: &additional_button
    text: "Additional button"
    id: "btn"

windows:
  MAIN:
    widgets:
      - text: "Different keyboard layouts."
      - switch_to:
          text: "↔️ Row"
          id: row
          state: Layouts:ROW
      - switch_to:
          text: "↕️ Column"
          id: column
          state: Layouts:COLUMN
      - switch_to:
          text: "↩️ Group"
          id: "group"
          state: Layouts:GROUP
      - start: !include components/menu_button.yaml
  ROW:
    widgets:
      - text: "Select and Button inside `Row`"
      - row:
          buttons:
            - select: *fruits_select
            - callback: *additional_button
      - switch_to: *back_button
  COLUMN:
    widgets:
      - text: "Select and Button inside `Column`"
      - column:
          buttons:
            - select: *fruits_select
            - callback: *additional_button
      - switch_to: *back_button
  GROUP:
    widgets:
      - text: "Select and Button inside `Group` with width=2"
      - group:
          width: 2
          buttons:
            - select: *fruits_select
            - callback: *additional_button
      - switch_to: *back_button
...
